Source: lorica-base
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Lorica Linux <lorica@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: lorica-base
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: apparmor, auditd, fail2ban, ufw, unattended-upgrades
Description: Lorica Linux base hardening configuration
 Security hardening for Debian servers. Installs drop-in configuration
 files for sysctl, GRUB boot parameters, kernel module blacklisting,
 and audit rules. Every setting is documented with its rationale and
 mapped to compliance frameworks (CIS, PCI-DSS, SOC 2, CNBV).
 .
 This package uses drop-in configs in /usr/lib/sysctl.d/,
 /etc/default/grub.d/, /etc/modprobe.d/, and /etc/audit/rules.d/.
 It never modifies files owned by other Debian packages.
